PARAGRAPH.#text: Among the companies with shares expected to actively trade in Thursday's session are Facebook Inc. FB, TripAdvisor Inc. (TRIP) and Sequenom Inc. SQNM. Facebook swung to a second-quarter profit as the world's largest social network continued building up its mobile advertising business and posted stronger revenue. Shares jumped 25% premarket to $32.67 as results easily beat market expectations. TripAdvisor's second-quarter earnings rose 26% as the hotel-reviews site recorded a surge in revenue. Headlines.Author: Michael Calia
Headlines.Headline: Assurant 2nd-Quarter Net Down 21% on Weakness in Noncore Units

PARAGRAPH.#text: Assurant Inc.'s AIZ second-quarter profit fell 21% as declines at its health and benefits businesses offset gains at its core specialty property business. Assurant, which is the largest seller of "force-placed" home insurance in the U.S., provides health, employee and property insurance as well as coverage for products like credit cards. The company's health business reported an 86% decline in income, mostly due to the year-ago quarter's benefiting from $13.9 million in investment income, while also reporting a decline in net earned premiums, fees and other items.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Assurant 2nd-Quarter Net Down 21% on Weakness in Noncore Units

Headlines.Headline: U.S. HOT STOCK FUTURES: HOT STOCKS TO WATCH

PARAGRAPH.#text: Among the companies with shares actively trading after hours are Zynga Inc. ZNGA, Angie's List Inc. ANGI and Best Buy Co. BBY. Zynga confirmed Wednesday it swung to a third-quarter loss as it continued to face challenges drawing bigger paying audiences to its free online social games. However, the San Francisco company's shares jumped 14% to $2.42 in late trading, as investors looked past its preannounced results and focused on a new share buyback plan and real-money gaming partnership in the U.K.

Headlines.Author: Tess Stynes
Headlines.Headline: Assurant 3Q Profit Up 71% on Improved Revenue, Lower Catastrophe Losses

PARAGRAPH.#text: Assurant Inc.'s AIZ third-quarter earnings rose 71%, as the insurer reported stronger revenue and sharply lower catastrophe losses from a year earlier. Profit rose to $126.3 million, or $1.52 a share, from $74 million, or 77 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenue increased 4% to $2.15 billion. Like others with exposure to homeowner insurance, the company, which provides health and life insurance, as well as coverage for other products such as credit cards, has benefited from fewer losses from catastrophes in recent quarters.

Headlines.Headline: Assurant Adds $600M To Stock Repurchase Plans

PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Assurant Inc.'s AIZ board added $600 million to its stock repurchase plans as the insurance company continues its efforts to reward shareholders. On Friday, Assurant unveiled plans to raise its quarterly dividend by 17% to 21 cents, a move that will cost the company about $10.3 million more a year. The company said the latest buyback authorization is in addition to about $170 million remaining under its existing share repurchase program. Assurant said it has repurchased 60.8 million shares for $2.4 billion since launching its first stock repurchase program in August 2004.

Headlines.Headline: Assurant Raises Quarterly Dividend 17%

PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Assurant Inc. AIZ raised its quarterly dividend by 17%, as the insurer looks to boost shareholder returns. The three-cent increase brings the company's quarterly payout to 21 cents a share and will cost the company about $10.3 million more a year. "The increased dividend is a reflection of both our ability to generate strong cash flows and deliver on our commitment to create increased value for our shareholders," said Chief Executive Robert B. Headlines.Headline: Assurant 3Q Net Off 46% On Catastrophe Losses In Specialty Property Unit

PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Assurant Inc.'s AIZ third-quarter earnings slid 46% as storms caused heavy catastrophe losses in its specialty property business and cut into the insurer's profit. Catastrophe losses for the business totaled $52.3 million for the third quarter. In addition, the company said the business was hampered by an increased frequency of noncatastrophe weather-related losses. At the same time, Assurant continued to struggle with falling premium revenue recently. In the latest period, premium revenue declined 3% from a year earlier.
